HPSJjl4TZx4.title: The Mile 22 Workout !
HPSJjl4TZx4.description:
Today's video is sponsored by Mile 22  

I saw Mile 22 and decided to model today's workout after this mind-blowing movie.  It's intense and unrelenting, just like the film.  I listed the "Mile 22 Workout" below so give it a try and let me know what you think!  Go see Mile 22 in theaters August 17th! 

The "Mile 22 Workout" - 

1. Deadlift 7-10 repetitions
2. Muscle Ups to failure
3. Dumbbell Press 7-10 reps
4. Pull Ups to Failure
5. Guillotine Press 7-10 reps
6. Neutral Grip Dumbbell press
7. Preacher Curls to Failure
8. Close Grip Bench Press to Failure 
9. Hold a Plank for 1-3 minutes
10. 50 Push Ups
11. Pause Box Jumps
12. Dips to Failure
13. Lat Pull Downs 
14. 22 Mile Run?

xuI75KugCho.description:
What are the best upper chest exercises? What is the best way to build the upper chest? Upper chest is in my opinion on of the hardest areas to build. For me it has taken me the longest, compared to other body parts. So over the years I have learned a few specific exercises that I've noticed have really helped me grow my upper chest and I believe most importantly help me contract me whole chest more strongly...creating a better mind muscle connection to the chest itself. I think this is one of the most important factors to bringing up lagging body parts and getting through plateaus is to create a stronger mind muscle connection with those lagging body parts. The upper chest for me was always one of the harder body parts to get to grow, but these are a few exercises that helped me change the game!

N60afb8F4NM.title: THE LAST WORKOUT OF 2016 |  Didn't get a photo w/ THE ROCK
N60afb8F4NM.description:
Total body workout for the last workout of 2016. I also met one of my role models. Dwayne the rock Johnson. Buuuut I froze up and forgot to ask for a photo! That's okay there is always next year..lol

Remember guys the most important thing about moving into a new year...or any new day for that matter is that it is a chance to get better as a person. A chance to change something you don't like. A chance to be who you've always wanted to or thought u could be. Don't wait every year until a new year to decided this is the year for a new me. That opportunity happens everyday...every moment. You make a decision to either live in happiness or to let whatever negative or hardships in your life control the next "few steps". Take a moment today to be thankful for it ALL....the good the bad and the ugly. Understand that you have the power to make the best out of any situation that will come in your life.

No one said this would be easy...and damnit it is not...but I promise you it will be worth it. Ive gone through some low times in my life and continue even today to be challenged. Losing a father at 6 years old to suicide is something that stays for a while on your mind. What I've learned about life over the last few years and a lot of what you guys have taught me and continue to teach me is that no matter where u come from and what you've dealt with...things CAN GET BETTER. Things WILL GET BETTER. So again take this day...(and everyday is year) to be a better version of yourself. Grow from your mistakes in 2016 and step forward into 2017 like a fucking champ. I love you guys. #letsgetbettertogether

_O_5RVhInPw.title: GET A BIGGER UPPER CHEST
_O_5RVhInPw.description:
The mysterious upper chest, what does it really take to build a bigger upper chest? Magic? Yes..well not really but sort of. Just kidding not at all. However it does take understanding your strong points and weak points of your pressing movements. Genetics obviously also play a roll in how quick your body can develop from certain training stimulus. However with all of that said, I found that changing up a few things has helped me to develop a stronger and thicker upper chest, for the looooongest time I seemed to have that sunken in chest flat chest syndrome and over time, changing the way I do things I was able to see growth. So understand at the end of the day, growing a bigger upper chest is still going to have to do with proper training consistency & nutrition...despite what changes you make to your training.

o5H2YADanUI.title: INCREASE YOUR DEADLIFT | GET A BIGGER BACK
o5H2YADanUI.description:
How to increase your deadlift, first of all...beyond any technique or proper form tutorials. Proper nutrition and rest is essential for any strength gains. While Increasing deadlift strength it is essential to focus on a few key things: 1. Keep your chest upright 2. Push the floor away (also somewhat drive your feet outwards..even if they don't move outwards it's the thought. 3. Keep the bar path tight.4. Warm up properly 5.Don't be a bitch. A proper training program is going to also be essential when trying to increase your deadlift or squat or bench or anything for that matter. Everything you do has an effect and can either set you up for victory when it comes to crushing your personal records. So make sure to set up your training program accordingly. Hopefully some of these tips can help you make those gains!!

IXDPmK-PcG0.title: I LOST A BET
IXDPmK-PcG0.description:
Lean BULK...I am still training as hard as I can. But learning that I seriously have to switch my training up a bit and really focus on recovery techniques. For so long it was just 100% go, without enough focus on the little things that help keep everything running smoothly, warming up properly, rehab/prehab work, mobility and flexibility work. These are all things I will  start incorporating daily. I am going to focus on more leg development while I give my upper back and upperbody a rest in general to allow some recovery techniques to really help. I know I know, everyday is ARM day. But for a few weeks I am going to have to focus on leg day..but that's okay. Sort of...anyways I appreciate all of the support as always. LETS GET BETTER TOGETHER. I will show u guys a ton more of the recovery techniques that I will be adding to my training program along the way to optimize my GAINZ, as well as focus on increasing my squat and deadlift over the next few weeks.
